hpicfNtpMIB.name: hpicfNtpMIB

revisions.description: Added new enum in following MIB object hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyAuthMode
Initial version of the MIB module.

hpicfNtpMIB.contactinfo: Hewlett-Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfNtpMIB.description: Management information for configuring the NTP client on Hewlett-Packard network devices.

hpicfNtpAdminStatus.name: hpicfNtpAdminStatus
hpicfNtpAdminStatus.description: When set to true, this enables NTP globally on the router. If set to false, this would disable NTP.

hpicfNtpConfigMode.name: hpicfNtpConfigMode
hpicfNtpConfigMode.description: The current operational mode of the NTP client.

hpicfNtpMaxAssociation.name: hpicfNtpMaxAssociation
hpicfNtpMaxAssociation.description: The maximum number of associations of the NTP client with different server's.

hpicfNtpStatusReferenceTimeFrac.name: hpicfNtpStatusReferenceTimeFrac
hpicfNtpStatusReferenceTimeFrac.description: The fractional part of the local time at which the local clock was last set or corrected. For example: a timestamp of 16.25 seconds would be stored as two Object IDs - the integer part 16 and the fraction part .25.

hpicfNtpStatusReferenceTimeSec.name: hpicfNtpStatusReferenceTimeSec
hpicfNtpStatusReferenceTimeSec.description: The integer part of the local time at which the local clock was last set or corrected. For example: timestamp of 16.25 seconds would be stored as two Object IDs - the integer part 16 and the fraction part .25.

hpicfNtpStatusClockOffset.name: hpicfNtpStatusClockOffset
hpicfNtpStatusClockOffset.description: The offset of the system clock, in milliseconds, to the synchronized peer.

hpicfNtpStatusRootDelay.name: hpicfNtpStatusRootDelay
hpicfNtpStatusRootDelay.description: The total round-trip delay, in milliseconds, to the primary reference source at the root of the synchronization.

hpicfNtpStatusRootDispersion.name: hpicfNtpStatusRootDispersion
hpicfNtpStatusRootDispersion.description: The root dispersion, in milliseconds, of the running NTP entity.

hpicfNtpAssoDrift.name: hpicfNtpAssoDrift
hpicfNtpAssoDrift.description: This is the rate of change in the system clock offset.

hpicfNtpInetConfigServerTable.name: hpicfNtpInetConfigServerTable
hpicfNtpInetConfigServerTable.description: A table containing trusted IPv4 or IPv6 NTP server's to be queried in unicast mode.

hpicfNtpInetServerAddressType.name: hpicfNtpInetServerAddressType
hpicfNtpInetServerAddressType.description: The IP address type of a trusted NTP server.

hpicfNtpInetServerAddress.name: hpicfNtpInetServerAddress
hpicfNtpInetServerAddress.description: The IP address of a trusted NTP server in which client communicates with server to synchorize its time. hpicfNtpInetServerAddress is always interpreted within the context of hpicfNtpInetServerAddressType.

hpicfNtpInetServerRowStatus.name: hpicfNtpInetServerRowStatus
hpicfNtpInetServerRowStatus.description: The row status of this NTP server information. Supporting CREATEANDGO and DESTROY only.

hpicfNtpInetServerAuthKeyId.name: hpicfNtpInetServerAuthKeyId
hpicfNtpInetServerAuthKeyId.description: The key identifier associated with the NTP server specified by this instance. It is an index to the hpicfntpAuthenticationKeyTable. The value identifies the row in the hpicfntpAuthenticationKeyTable where the authentication key can be found. The value '0' indicates that the key-id is disassociated from the NTP server.

hpicfNtpConfigPollMinInterval.name: hpicfNtpConfigPollMinInterval
hpicfNtpConfigPollMinInterval.description: Period of time between successive attempts to perform an update via NTP.

hpicfNtpConfigPollMaxInterval.name: hpicfNtpConfigPollMaxInterval
hpicfNtpConfigPollMaxInterval.description: Maximum period of time between successive attempts to perform an update via NTP.

hpicfNtpAssoBurst.name: hpicfNtpAssoBurst
hpicfNtpAssoBurst.description: This option is used for, to speed up the initial synchronization acquisition with the server, Below are different options supported. noburst - Burst not set, Polling happens with configured or default poll interval. burst - Send a burst of eight packets instead of the usual one packet. The interval between the first and the second packets is about 16 seconds to allow a modem call to complete, while the spacing between the remaining packets is about 2s. iburst - Send a burst of eight packets instead of the usual one. As long as the server is unreachable, the interval between packets is about 16 seconds to allow a modem call to complete. After the server is reachable, the spacing between packets is about 2 seconds.

hpicfNtpAssoIsOobm.name: hpicfNtpAssoIsOobm
hpicfNtpAssoIsOobm.description: This object indicates whether this NTP Server is reachable over OOBM (Out Of Band Management) interface or not. This mib object will be applicable only if there is a physical OOBM port on the device.

hpicfNtpInetServerInfoTable.name: hpicfNtpInetServerInfoTable
hpicfNtpInetServerInfoTable.description: A table containing trusted IPv4 or IPv6 NTP server's information.

hpicfNtpAssoPeerPollInterval.name: hpicfNtpAssoPeerPollInterval
hpicfNtpAssoPeerPollInterval.description: Poll interval from peer to the local machine.

hpicfNtpAssoRootDelay.name: hpicfNtpAssoRootDelay
hpicfNtpAssoRootDelay.description: Delay in, milliseconds, to the root of the NTP setup. Stratum 1 clocks are considered to be at the root of an NTP setup/design.

hpicfNtpAssoRootDispersion.name: hpicfNtpAssoRootDispersion
hpicfNtpAssoRootDispersion.description: Maximum clock time difference that was ever observed between the local clock and the root clock.

hpicfNtpAssoPeerReach.name: hpicfNtpAssoPeerReach
hpicfNtpAssoPeerReach.description: The reachability register of the remote association, in octal format. This number is determined by the NTP algorithm.

hpicfNtpAssoOriginTimeFrac.name: hpicfNtpAssoOriginTimeFrac
hpicfNtpAssoOriginTimeFrac.description: It is the fractional part of this client time stamp when the request was sent to the server after the poll interval. For example: a timestamp of 16.25 seconds would be stored as two Object IDs - the integer part 16 and the fraction part .25.

hpicfNtpAssoOriginTimeSec.name: hpicfNtpAssoOriginTimeSec
hpicfNtpAssoOriginTimeSec.description: It is integer part of this client time stamp when the request was sent to the server after the poll interval. For example: a timestamp of 16.25 seconds would be stored as two Object IDs - the integer part 16 and the fraction part .25.

hpicfNtpAssoRecvTimeFrac.name: hpicfNtpAssoRecvTimeFrac
hpicfNtpAssoRecvTimeFrac.description: This is fractional part of the time stamp when the local client received the message. The difference between the origin time and the receive time is the offset for this peer. For example: a timestamp of 16.25 seconds would be stored as two Object IDs - the integer part 16 and the fraction part .25.

hpicfNtpAssoRecvTimeSec.name: hpicfNtpAssoRecvTimeSec
hpicfNtpAssoRecvTimeSec.description: This is the integer part of time stamp when the local client received the message. The difference between the origin time and the receive time is the offset for this peer. For example: a timestamp of 16.25 seconds would be stored as two Object IDs - the integer part 16 and the fraction part .25.

hpicfNtpAssoXmtTimeFrac.name: hpicfNtpAssoXmtTimeFrac
hpicfNtpAssoXmtTimeFrac.description: This is the fractional part of the server's time stamp for the NTP packet when it sends back the packet to the client. For example: a timestamp of 16.25 seconds would be stored as two Object IDs - the integer part 16 and the fraction part .25.

hpicfNtpAssoXmtTimeSec.name: hpicfNtpAssoXmtTimeSec
hpicfNtpAssoXmtTimeSec.description: This is the integer part of the server's time stamp for the NTP packet when it sends back the packet to the client. For example: a timestamp of 16.25 seconds would be stored as two Object IDs - the integer part 16 and the fraction part .25.

hpicfNtpAssolastPollreq.name: hpicfNtpAssolastPollreq
hpicfNtpAssolastPollreq.description: This is the time in seconds since the last NTP packet was received from a peer is reported. This value should be lower than the polling interval.

hpicfNtpAssoPrecision.name: hpicfNtpAssoPrecision
hpicfNtpAssoPrecision.description: This is the precision of the peer clock in Hz.

hpicfNtpAssoCurrentMode.name: hpicfNtpAssoCurrentMode
hpicfNtpAssoCurrentMode.description: The current mode of the NTP. The definition of each possible value as follows: notsynchronized(2) - NTP is not synchronized to any time source (stratum = 16). synchronized(1) - NTP is synchronized. unknown(99) - The state of NTP is unknown.

hpicfNtpAssoPeerDispersion.name: hpicfNtpAssoPeerDispersion
hpicfNtpAssoPeerDispersion.description: The estimated maximum error of the peer clock relative to the local clock over the network path between them, in seconds. This value is determined by using NTP clock-filter algorithm.

hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyTable.name: hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyTable
hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyTable.description: A table containing entries of authentication key-id. The number of key-id is restricted to 8.

hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyEntry.name: hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyEntry
hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyEntry.description: An authentication key entry comprising key-identifiers such as key-id, key-value, authentication mode (MD5/SHA1), and status of the key-id if it is trusted or not.

hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyId.name: hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyId
hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyId.description: A unique identifier for the authentication key.

hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyAuthMode.name: hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyAuthMode
hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyAuthMode.description: The authentication mode supported by this key.

hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyValue.name: hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyValue
hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyValue.description: A unique string that serves as the key-value for generating the message digest sent in the NTP packet. A read on this object will return an empty string.

hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyTrusted.name: hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyTrusted
hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyTrusted.description: This object is used to configure the status of the authentication key as trusted. If the key-value is not trusted, the packet is not trusted. By default, the key-value is not trusted.

hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyRowStatus.name: hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyRowStatus
hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyRowStatus.description: The row status for this NTP authentication key instance. The key-id is the index and it cannot be edited. Supporting CREATEANDGO and DESTROY only.

hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyEncrypted.name: hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyEncrypted
hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyEncrypted.description: The encrypted form of a unique string that serves as the key-value for generating the message digest sent in the NTP packet. This object may only be read or written when hpSwitchAuthenticationEncryptCredentialsMethod is set to a value other than none(0). This object should only be written with an encrypted key previously read from a compatible HP Networking device.

hpicfNtpIpv6MulticastTable.name: hpicfNtpIpv6MulticastTable
hpicfNtpIpv6MulticastTable.description: A table containing entry for enabling NTP multicast.

hpicfNtpIpv6MulticastEntry.name: hpicfNtpIpv6MulticastEntry
hpicfNtpIpv6MulticastEntry.description: An NTP multicast entry comprising NTP multicast on vlan.

hpicfNtpIpv6Multicast.name: hpicfNtpIpv6Multicast
hpicfNtpIpv6Multicast.description: Indicates whether this interface should listen to NTP multicast packets.

hpicfNtpIpv6MulticastStatus.name: hpicfNtpIpv6MulticastStatus
hpicfNtpIpv6MulticastStatus.description: Row status of the NTP Multicast. Supporting CREATEANDGO and DESTROY only.

hpicfNtpAssoSampleTable.name: hpicfNtpAssoSampleTable
hpicfNtpAssoSampleTable.description: A table containing samples for association.

hpicfNtpAssoSampleEntry.name: hpicfNtpAssoSampleEntry
hpicfNtpAssoSampleEntry.description: An association sample entry comprising 8 samples of each association for filter delay and offset.

hpicfNtpAssoSampleId.name: hpicfNtpAssoSampleId
hpicfNtpAssoSampleId.description: The sample Id for every sample per association.

hpicfNtpfiltDelaySample.name: hpicfNtpfiltDelaySample
hpicfNtpfiltDelaySample.description: The round trip delay of the sample of this association.

hpicfNtpfiltOffsetSample.name: hpicfNtpfiltOffsetSample
hpicfNtpfiltOffsetSample.description: The offset of the sample of this association.

hpicfNtpInetServerNameTable.name: hpicfNtpInetServerNameTable
hpicfNtpInetServerNameTable.description: A table containing trusted IPv4 or IPv6 NTP server's to be queried in unicast mode.

hpicfNtpServerNameIndex.name: hpicfNtpServerNameIndex
hpicfNtpServerNameIndex.description: The index of a NTP unicast server name in hpicfNtpInetServerNameTable. The maximum number of server name configurabile is 8.

hpicfNtpInetServerNameRowStatus.name: hpicfNtpInetServerNameRowStatus
hpicfNtpInetServerNameRowStatus.description: The row status of this NTP server information. Supporting CREATEANDGO and DESTROY only.

hpicfNtpServerNameResolvAddType.name: hpicfNtpServerNameResolvAddType
hpicfNtpServerNameResolvAddType.description: The IP address type of a DNS resolved NTP server name.

hpicfNtpServerNameResolvAddress.name: hpicfNtpServerNameResolvAddress
hpicfNtpServerNameResolvAddress.description: The IP address of a DNS resolved NTP server name in which client communicates with server to synchorize its time.

hpicfNtpServerNameResolveStatus.name: hpicfNtpServerNameResolveStatus
hpicfNtpServerNameResolveStatus.description: This object indicates the NTP Server name resolution status. The definition of each possible value as follows: notattempted(0) - DNS resolution is not attempted for the NTP server name. active(1) - DNS resolution succeeded for the NTP server name and the NTP server is active. dnsunknownhost(2) - DNS resolution failed with unknown host for the NTP server name. dnsnotresponding(3) - DNS server is not responding for the NTP server name. dnsfailed(4) - DNS resolution failed for the NTP server name. notactive(5) - DNS resolution succeeded for the NTP server name but the NTP server is not active.

hpicfNtpInetServerNameAuthKeyId.name: hpicfNtpInetServerNameAuthKeyId
hpicfNtpInetServerNameAuthKeyId.description: The key identifier associated with the NTP server specified by this instance. It is an index to the hpicfntpAuthenticationKeyTable. The value identifies the row in the hpicfntpAuthenticationKeyTable where the authentication key can be found. The value '0' indicates that the key-id is disassociated from the NTP server.

hpicfNtpConfigServerNamePollMinInterval.name: hpicfNtpConfigServerNamePollMinInterval
hpicfNtpConfigServerNamePollMinInterval.description: Period of time between successive attempts to perform an update via NTP.

hpicfNtpConfigServerNamePollMaxInterval.name: hpicfNtpConfigServerNamePollMaxInterval
hpicfNtpConfigServerNamePollMaxInterval.description: Maximum period of time between successive attempts to perform an update via NTP.

hpicfNtpServerNameAssoBurst.name: hpicfNtpServerNameAssoBurst
hpicfNtpServerNameAssoBurst.description: This option is used for, to speed up the initial synchronization acquisition with the server, Below are different options supported. noburst - Burst not set, Polling happens with configured or default poll interval. burst - Send a burst of eight packets instead of the usual one packet. The interval between the first and the second packets is about 16 seconds to allow a modem call to complete, while the spacing between the remaining packets is about 2s. iburst - Send a burst of eight packets instead of the usual one. As long as the server is unreachable, the interval between packets is about 16 seconds to allow a modem call to complete. After the server is reachable, the spacing between packets is about 2 seconds.

hpicfNtpServerNameAssoIsOobm.name: hpicfNtpServerNameAssoIsOobm
hpicfNtpServerNameAssoIsOobm.description: This object indicates whether this NTP Server name is reachable over OOBM (Out Of Band Management) interface or not. This mib object will be applicable only if there is a physical OOBM port on the device.

hpicfNtpInetConfigCompliance.name: hpicfNtpInetConfigCompliance
hpicfNtpInetConfigCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices implementing the hpicfNtpConfig MIB.

hpicfNtpAuthenticationConfigCompliance.name: hpicfNtpAuthenticationConfigCompliance
hpicfNtpAuthenticationConfigCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices implementing the hpicfNtpConfig MIB.

hpicfNtpServerConfigCompliance.name: hpicfNtpServerConfigCompliance
hpicfNtpServerConfigCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices implementing the hpicfNtpConfig MIB.

hpicfNtpAssoSampleCompliance.name: hpicfNtpAssoSampleCompliance
hpicfNtpAssoSampleCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices implementing the hpicfNtpConfig MIB.

hpicfNtpServerNameCfgCompliance.name: hpicfNtpServerNameCfgCompliance
hpicfNtpServerNameCfgCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices implementing the hpicfNtpConfig MIB.

hpicfNtpConfigGroup.name: hpicfNtpConfigGroup
hpicfNtpConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects for configuring the NTP client.

hpicfNtpInetServerConfigGroup.name: hpicfNtpInetServerConfigGroup
hpicfNtpInetServerConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects for configuring the NTP server entry.

hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyIdConfigGroup.name: hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyIdConfigGroup
hpicfNtpAuthenticationKeyIdConfigGroup.description: This group defines NTP authentication related information. It includes Key-Identifier, Key-Value, encrypted key value, flag to indicate whether the information is trusted or not and whether the authentication mode(MD5/SHA1) currently supported.

hpicfNtpAssociationSampleGroup.name: hpicfNtpAssociationSampleGroup
hpicfNtpAssociationSampleGroup.description: This group defines sample information for eight samples taken per association.

hpicfNtpInetServerNameCfgGroup.name: hpicfNtpInetServerNameCfgGroup
hpicfNtpInetServerNameCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects for configuring the NTP server Name entry.
